AB  - This paper provides a general equilibrium model for examining the individual as well as the joint effects of export requirements and local equity controls of multinational firms. The results suggest that for a small open economy under tariff protection, the desirable policy is 100% foreign ownership of subsidiaries, coupled with an export-share requirement.
